# Traza Tools Frontend — Core Standards

## Stack
- Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS v4, shadcn/ui (base-ui primitives)
- SWR for data fetching, `@/lib/api-client` for all HTTP

## Architecture
- Module-first: `src/modules/[domain]/{components,hooks,services,types}`
- Global: `src/components/ui/` (shadcn), `src/lib/` (api-client, auth-context, types, utils)
- Routes: `src/app/(dashboard)/dashboard/[section]/page.tsx`

## Rules

**Services** — all API calls through class-based services, never `fetch` in components:
```ts
class FooService {
  private readonly basePath = '/api/v1/foos'
  async getAll() { return apiClient.get<Foo[]>(`${this.basePath}/`) }
}
export const fooService = new FooService()
```

**Components** — always use `@/components/ui/` (shadcn) over native HTML elements.

**Imports** — always absolute (`@/modules/...`), never relative (`../../`).

**Constants** — no magic numbers; name them.

**Early returns** — prefer guard clauses over nested ifs.

**No copy-paste** — extract to hook, util, or component.

## shadcn/ui (base-ui) API — IMPORTANT
This project uses shadcn v4 with base-ui primitives. Key differences from Radix-based shadcn:

- **No `asChild` prop** — use `render` prop instead:
  ```tsx
  // ❌ <DropdownMenuTrigger asChild><button>...</button></DropdownMenuTrigger>
  // ✅
  <DropdownMenuTrigger render={<div>...</div>} />
  ```
- **`SidebarMenuButton`** uses `render` prop, not `asChild`
- **`Button`** also uses `render` prop — use `<Button render={<Link href="..." />}>label</Button>` for link buttons
- **`TooltipProvider`** uses `delay` prop, not `delayDuration`
- Never nest `<button>` inside `<button>` — use `<div>` as trigger render target
